sudo -i

apt-get update

java

sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y openjdk-17-jdk


sudo wget -O /etc/apt/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc   https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable/jenkins.io-2026.key
echo "deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc]"   https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable binary/ | sudo tee   /etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list > /dev/null

sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y jenkins
systemctl status jenkins



---------------------------------------------------

1. Jenkins Master is configured on a VM running Ubuntu 24.04 LTS hosted on Google Cloud Platform (GCP).
2. On the Jenkins Master, agent communication is configured to use a random port
(Jenkins → Manage Jenkins → Security → Agents → Select “Random”).
3.Java 17 JDK is installed on all Jenkins agent (slave) machines.
4. In AWS security groups, outbound access is allowed on ports 8080 and 443.
5. The first Jenkins agent is configured on a Windows Server 2025 VM in AWS, with the workspace located at:
C:\jenkins\developer
6. The second Jenkins agent is configured on a VM running Ubuntu 24.04 LTS in GCP, with the workspace located at:
/var/jenkins/performance

